---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import Lede from '../components/Lede.astro';
import RelatedLinks from '../components/RelatedLinks.astro';
---

<Base
  title="The Trilogy — Eidos AGI"
  description="Three tools enforce one contract: governance before action, evidence before decisions, tracking after execution."
>
    <article class="prose-page">
      <PageHero title="The Trilogy" subtitle="Governance. Decisions. Execution." status="shipped" />
      <Lede text="Three tools that turn agent improvisation into auditable, evidence-based execution. Research earns decisions. Visionlog records contracts. Ike executes." />

      <!-- Pipeline diagram -->
      <div class="tri-page-diagram">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 500 320" fill="none" role="img" aria-label="The trilogy: research.md earns decisions, visionlog records contracts, ike.md executes within them. Governance contracts feed back to govern the entire loop.">
          <rect class="tp-node tp-n1" x="170" y="10" width="160" height="60" rx="3"/>
          <text class="tp-label" x="250" y="47" text-anchor="middle">visionlog</text>
          <text class="tp-sub" x="250" y="30" text-anchor="middle">GOVERNANCE</text>

          <rect class="tp-node tp-n2" x="170" y="120" width="160" height="60" rx="3"/>
          <text class="tp-label" x="250" y="157" text-anchor="middle">research.md</text>
          <text class="tp-sub" x="250" y="140" text-anchor="middle">DECISIONS</text>

          <rect class="tp-node tp-n3" x="170" y="230" width="160" height="60" rx="3"/>
          <text class="tp-label" x="250" y="267" text-anchor="middle">ike.md</text>
          <text class="tp-sub" x="250" y="250" text-anchor="middle">EXECUTION</text>

          <!-- Arrows down -->
          <line class="tp-arrow" x1="250" y1="70" x2="250" y2="120"/>
          <polygon class="tp-head" points="244,114 250,124 256,114"/>
          <line class="tp-arrow" x1="250" y1="180" x2="250" y2="230"/>
          <polygon class="tp-head" points="244,224 250,234 256,224"/>

          <!-- Feedback loop -->
          <path class="tp-feedback" d="M330 260 Q400 260 400 200 Q400 140 400 80 Q400 40 330 40"/>

          <!-- Side labels -->
          <text class="tp-side" x="155" y="100" text-anchor="end">sets constraints</text>
          <text class="tp-side" x="155" y="210" text-anchor="end">earns decisions</text>
          <text class="tp-side" x="415" y="150" text-anchor="start">contracts govern</text>
        </svg>
      </div>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>The contract</h2>
        <p>Agents don't get to skip governance, guess at decisions, or lose track of execution. The trilogy enforces that contract with three tools, each handling one concern:</p>
        <ul class="tri-page-list">
          <li><strong>visionlog</strong> records what the project has committed to — vision, goals, guardrails, ADRs. If a task would violate a guardrail, the answer is already no.</li>
          <li><strong>research.md</strong> earns decisions with evidence. Candidates are scored against locked criteria. The research is the receipt.</li>
          <li><strong>ike.md</strong> executes tasks within those contracts. Every task links to the goal it serves. Definition of Done is explicit, not assumed.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>The flow</h2>
        <p>The three tools aren't a pipeline — they're a dance. Research can trigger new guardrails. Execution can surface findings that reopen research. Governance evolves from what execution discovers. Each tool can be used alone, but new capabilities emerge when they work together.</p>
        <p>A decision earned in research.md becomes a contract in visionlog. A guardrail in visionlog constrains what ike.md can execute. A task completed in ike.md can surface evidence that feeds back into research.md. The loop is continuous, not linear.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Install</h2>
        <pre><code>pip install visionlog-md research-md ike-md</code></pre>
        <p>Three packages. One contract. Each is an MCP server — agents read and write governance through tool calls.</p>
        <div class="tri-page-links">
          <a href="/tools/visionlog">visionlog docs</a>
          <a href="/tools/research">research.md docs</a>
          <a href="/tools/ike">ike.md docs</a>
        </div>
      </section>
      <RelatedLinks links={[
        { href: "/tools/visionlog", label: "visionlog docs" },
        { href: "/tools/research", label: "research.md docs" },
        { href: "/tools/ike", label: "ike.md docs" },
        { href: "/contract-driven-development", label: "Contracts" },
        { href: "/eidos", label: "Eidos" },
      ]} />
    </article>
</Base>

<style is:global>
  .tri-page-diagram {
    margin: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-8);
    max-width: 500px;
  }
  .tri-page-diagram svg { width: 100%; height: auto; }
  .tp-node {
    fill: var(--color-surface);
    stroke: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 30%, transparent);
    stroke-width: 1;
  }
  .tp-n1 { stroke: var(--color-primary); }
  .tp-n2 { stroke: var(--color-primary); opacity: 0.8; }
  .tp-n3 { stroke: var(--color-primary); opacity: 0.6; }
  .tp-label {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 16px;
    fill: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .tp-sub {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 8px;
    fill: var(--color-primary);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  }
  .tp-arrow {
    stroke: var(--color-primary);
    stroke-width: 1.5;
    stroke-dasharray: 4 3;
    animation: tp-dash 1.5s linear infinite;
  }
  .tp-head { fill: var(--color-primary); }
  .tp-feedback {
    stroke: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-primary) 30%, transparent);
    stroke-width: 1;
    stroke-dasharray: 3 4;
    fill: none;
    animation: tp-dash 3s linear infinite reverse;
  }
  .tp-side {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 9px;
    fill: var(--color-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  @keyframes tp-dash { to { stroke-dashoffset: -14; } }

  .tri-page-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: var(--space-6) 0;
  }
  .tri-page-list li {
    padding: var(--space-3) 0;
    border-bottom: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 10%, transparent);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }
  .tri-page-list li strong {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .tri-page-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
  }
  .tri-page-links a { color: var(--color-muted); }
  .tri-page-links a:hover { color: var(--color-primary); }
</style>
